                <h3>Technology Origins</h3>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li><strong>Innovation:</strong> Created by outdoor survival expert Jim Phillips</li>
                    <li><strong>Core Material:</strong> Uses open-cell polyurethane foam insulation</li>
                    <li><strong>Applications:</strong> Successfully tested in various gear including jackets, hoods, pants, boots, gloves, and sleeping bags</li>
                </ul>
            
                <h3>Key Features</h3>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li><strong>Life-Saving Protection:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Maintains warmth even in freezing temperatures</li>
                            <li>Effective insulation even when wet</li>
                            <li>Dramatically reduces cold-related risks</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Technical Design:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Synthetic shell and lining materials</li>
                            <li>Breathable construction for moisture wicking</li>
                            <li>Allows perspiration to evaporate naturally</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            
                <h3>The Turtle Shelter Difference</h3>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Traditional foam clothing is typically expensive and marketed for emergency preparedness and extreme sports</li>
                    <li><strong>Our Mission:</strong> Making this life-saving technology available to those who need it most</li>
                    <li><strong>Design Focus:</strong> Core-warming vest design that functions as a portable shelter</li>
                </ul>
            
                <blockquote class="impact-quote">
                    <p>"Isn't a person who is homeless living in their emergency right this very moment? They are not waiting for disaster to strike because for them it already has..."</p>
                    <footer>- Jen's Perspective</footer>
